cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with active learning for binary label prediction on a graph, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a novel algorithm for this task, which involves graph-based techniques and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The algorithm also involves selecting vertices based on the structure of the graph, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant category. The paper also presents theoretical estimates and complexity analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
